section.para:
If we can reproduce your problem, you are much more likely to
get a fix in a reasonable time.  So the more information you
provide, the better.  Please give us:




      the skit version;





      a short description of the problem;





      the RDBMS version;





     instructions for reproducing the problem;



      Copies of the source xml files, or a pg_dump, without
      data, of the source database would be very useful, though
      if these are large files, it would be better to offer them
      and wait for a response from the developers.





      any clues	you can provide based on your attempts to get
      around the issue.
